        "body": "## Summary\n- implements multi-account primitives across RepoBarCore: `Account`, `AccountSelection`, account-scoped repository lists, and settings migration fields\n- adds account-aware app plumbing with `AccountManager`, legacy OAuth/PAT migration, per-account token refresh, session aggregation state, and account list UI controls\n- extends CLI account management with `repobar accounts list/use/remove`, `--account` support on auth/status paths, and account-scoped token persistence for login/import flows\n- partitions cache helper APIs by account ID while preserving legacy defaults\n- adds focused tests for account ID/API host derivation, account selection/settings Codable behavior, account-scoped repo lists, and CLI account resolution\n- updates auth storage, CLI, plan docs, and changelog to match the implementation\n\n## Validation\n- `git diff --check`\n- Claude Code Opus static compile/integration review pass over the full diff\n- `pnpm test -- --filter AccountModelTests` attempted, but this Linux host has no Swift toolchain: `./Scripts/test.sh: line 13: swift: command not found`\n\n## Notes\n- Draft remains open because macOS/Xcode Swift compilation still needs to run in CI or on a macOS dev host.\n",
